<br>
When you acquire all 10 shards you will need a piece of luclinite and a rift from the Emperor.  Please contact me in game for these once shards are completed.  You will need to combine these in a frame which is quested in Akheva.  If you need assistance to acquire the frame (once all 10 shards are done) please contact me in game and I will help you.<br>
<br>
==============================================<br>
<br>
Vex Thal shards can be found in the following, you'll need one of each:<br>
<br>
1. Ssra --- Basement mines. Can be off any skeletons but high drop rate on skeleton drudges, which are in the back half of the mines. (uncommon)<br>
2. Sanctus Seru --- all the legionnaires etc. At zone is good for solo, go in a bit and go up via telepad to kill around the ring wall is good for group. (rare) <br>
3. Fungus Grove --- Warriors/Royal (lvl 60 only) (rare)<br>
4. Dawnshroud --- Rockhopper/Sambata cave, either can drop (common)<br>
5. The Grey --- Named Rockfiend, Sun Revs at NE corner around lake. (uncommon)<br>
6. Scarlet Desert --- Sun Rev/Reavers (common)<br>
7. Akheva --- Shaded Rock, Roudy Ruble, Xi Vius, Xi Xiau, Shadow Reaver etc. Either camp Va Dyn room or IV prep room. (uncommon)<br>
8. The Deep --- Any though horrors. Best drop rate is pass the invis bridge near THO area before Elder Thought Horrors. (uncommon)<br>
9. Acrylia --- 2 Skullcracker/Runed at the city gates. So far only seen shard drop from those 2 spawns. (uncommon)<br>
10. Maiden's Eye --- Goranga Prophet, Battlemaster, Seer, Forager, Savant. Not 100% drop. PH for the goranga named are Goranga Scouts. (very rare) This is the bottle neck shard.<br>
<br>
If you buy/trade for them, these are what they identify as:<br>
Dat...Fungus Grove<br>
Dax...Akheva Ruins<br>
Kel...The Grey<br>
Kelera...Sanctus Seru/Katta<br>
Lor...Dawnshroud Peaks<br>
Raf...The Deep<br>
Set...Scarlet Desert<br>
Tek...Maiden's Eye<br>
Ved...Acrylia Caverns<br>
Vin...Ssraeshza Temple  <p>Is that a feint or a parry? For a man who prays for my mortal demise, I'd recommend a sharper step and keener concentration.<br>
